This topic describes how to install and configure Aerospike EE Managed Service for PCF, 
as well as how to view the admin credentials of your Aerospike database.

##<a id='install'></a> Install and Configure Aerospike EE Managed Service for PCF 

To install and configure the Aerospike EE Managed Service tile, perform the following steps:

1. Download the product file from [Pivotal Network](https://network.pivotal.io/products/aerospike-ee-managed-service/).

1. Upload the product file on the Ops Manager Installation Dashboard.

1. Click **Add** next to the uploaded Aerospike EE Managed Service tile in the Ops Manager **Available Products** view to add it to your staging area.
    <br><%= image_tag('add-tile.png') %>

1. Click the newly added **Aerospike EE Managed Service** tile.
    <br><%= image_tag('tile.png') %>

1. From the **Settings** tab, click **Namespaces**.
    <br><%= image_tag('namespace-tab.png') %>

1. Click on the default namespace to configure a new namespace.
    <br><%= image_tag('default-ns.png') %>

1. To add additional namespaces click the **Add** button to create a namespace for the database.
    <br><%= image_tag('ns-add.png') %>

1. Enter the **Namespace Name** and then verify the default settings or change them as required.
    <br><%= image_tag('ns-config1.png') %>
    <br><%= image_tag('ns-config2.png') %>
    <p class="note"><strong>Note</strong>: For more information about configuring namespaces, see the Aerospike [documentation](http://www.aerospike.com/docs/operations/configure/namespace).</p> 

1. Continue adding and configuring namespaces until all namespaces required for this deployment have been configured.

1. Click **Save**.

1. From the **Settings** tab, click **Aerospike Network Configuration**.
    <br><%= image_tag('network-tab.png') %>

1. Verify the default network configuration settings or change them as required.
    <br><%= image_tag('network-config.png') %>
    <p class="note"><strong>Note</strong>: For more information on the network configuration, view the Aerospike [documentation](http://www.aerospike.com/docs/operations/configure/network).</p>

1. Click **Save**.

1. From the **Settings** tab, click **Aerospike Service Configuration**.
    <br><%= image_tag('service-tab.png') %>

1. Verify the default service configuration settings or change them as required.
    <br><%= image_tag('service-config.png') %>
    <p class="note"><strong>Note</strong>: For more information on the service configuration, view the Aerospike [documentation](http://www.aerospike.com/docs/reference/configuration).</p>
    <p class="note"><strong>Note</strong>: Make sure to enter your Aerospike Feature Key into the text area at the bottom of the service configuration tab.</p>

1. Click **Save**.


1. From the **Settings** tab, click **Resource Config**.
    <br><%= image_tag('resource-tab.png') %>

1. The **Resource Config** panel allows you to configure the size of the database cluster by setting the number of instances for the **aerospike_server** job.
    <br><%= image_tag('res-config.png') %>

1. You can also configure the disk type for each of the VMs in the cluster on the **Resource Config** panel.
    <br><%= image_tag('disk-type.png') %>

1. Finally, you can choose the VM type for each of the VMs in the cluster on the **Resource Config** panel.
    <br><%= image_tag('vm-type.png') %>

1. Click **Save**.
1. Return to the Ops Manager Installation Dashboard and click **Apply Changes** to install the Aerospike EE Managed Service tile.

##<a id='credentials'></a> View the Admin Database Credentials

To view the admin credentials of your Aerospike database, perform the following steps:

1. Click on the **Credetials** tab on the tile configuration.
    <br><%= image_tag('creds-tab.png') %>

1. For the **aerospike_server** job, click the **Link to Credential** for the **Db Credentials**.
    <br><%= image_tag('db-creds.png') %>

1. The credentials for the **admin** user display as JSON.
    <br><%= image_tag('admin-creds.png') %>
